Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.14,0:00:07.52,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}We were playing football at a park to get some exercise while waiting for a cake to arrive at Dr. Agasa's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:16.93,Narr,,10,10,0,,{\blur3}But then, chasing after Taii, the cat who made its home at Café Poirot, we ended up shut in the back of a refrigerated delivery van.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.18,0:00:22.04,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}On top of that, Haibara's handmade sweater unravelled,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.04,0:00:26.83,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}and with her in no sight to be seen, we ended up unable to leave even if we wanted to...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.43,0:00:32.88,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Then, we found a man's corpse among the items in the van.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:38.64,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}We attempted to tell the police using Mitsuhiko's phone, but the battery ran out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.32,0:00:44.81,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}We then decided to think of some way to get a message outside using what we had at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（歩美）歩美が持ってたのは→\N\Nハンカチとポケットティッシュと\Nキャンディーと綿棒。\N}I've got a handkerchief, pocket tissues, a piece of candy, and a cotton bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.60,0:00:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{フム…元太は？\N}And you, Genta?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.34,0:01:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（元太）\Nえ～っと　俺は}Let's see. {バンソウコウと→\N\Nチョコバーと\Nしもやけのかゆみ止め。\N}I've got a plaster, a chocolate bar, and an anti-itch cream for frostnips!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.38,0:01:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{で　光彦は？}And you, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.17,0:01:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（光彦）僕はですね→\N}{手帳と　それに付けてる\Nボールペンと→\N}I have a notebook with a ball point pen, {ハンカチと　お財布と\Nタクシーのレシートです。\N}a handkerchief, a wallet, and a taxi receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.98,0:01:15.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{《ん？確かこの猫…》\N}Come to think of it, this cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.59,0:01:19.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{《あっ　そうか！その手が！！》\N}Aha! I know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（灰原）何？何か思いついたんなら\N言いなさいよ！\N}What? If you thought of something, spit it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.73,0:01:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{えっ？ああ…}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.35,0:01:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{１つ前に\Nこの宅配便の車が止まったのは→\N}The last stops made by this delivery van {３丁目の米花マンションでさっきは４丁目の家２軒。\N}were to Beika House{condominium is a form of parliament in British English} in the third district, then to two houses in the fourth district.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.63,0:01:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{んじゃ　次は？\N}So what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.08,0:01:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ご　５丁目じゃないでしょうか？\N}W-Wouldn't it be the fifth district, I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.97,0:01:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そう！}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.59,0:01:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{この猫の大尉の根城。\N}The home of this cat, Taii.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.58,0:01:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{夕方になると　餌をねだりに行く喫茶ポアロがある５丁目だ！\N}The fifth district, home to Café Poirot, where it goes to beg for food in the evenings!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.62,0:01:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そっか！大ちゃんに助けてって\N手紙を届けてもらうんだね！\N}I see! We'll let Tai-{\i1}chan{\i0} deliver a piece of paper saying 'Help'!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.33,0:01:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{首輪に挟んでおけば　きっと梓さん気づいてくれますよ！！\N}If we stick it in its collar, I bet Azusa-{\i1}san{\i0} will notice it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:01:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{それで行こうぜ！}Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.45,0:02:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ！\N}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（灰原）でも…。\Nあ！？\N}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.52,0:02:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{もしも　このコが\Nここから出る時に→\N}If those two catch this kitty sneaking out {あの２人に捕まって\N紙に気づかれたら…。\N}and notice the piece of paper...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そこんとこは　抜かりね～よ。えっ？\N}We won't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.55,0:02:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あいつらに見られても\N気づかれねぇ→\N\N暗号を作ってやっから。\N}I'll make a code that they won't figure out, even if they {\i1}do{\i0} see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.22,0:02:34.13,BCPrologue,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{＜影の黒さと闇の濃さ\N切り裂いてくのが推理の光＞\N}Only the light of deductions can tear apart black shadows and deep darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.13,0:02:38.00,BCPrologue,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Where will the code deciding the fate of the Detective Boys end up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:39.47,BCPrologue,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{＜たった１つの真実　見抜く\N}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.47,0:02:41.44,BCPrologue,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}{見た目は子供　頭脳は大人＞\N}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.44,0:02:43.36,BCPrologue,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\fad(0,250)}{＜その名は　名探偵コナン！＞\N}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.75,0:04:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.73,0:04:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The taxi receipt Mitsuhiko had was printed on thermal paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.90,0:04:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than using ink, it turns black when heated to form words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The front of thermal paper is coated with a chemical that turns black, and another acidic chemical called the colour former.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:38.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When exposed to heat, the colour former melts and the two chemicals react, causing words to appear in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.12,0:04:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the ammonia in the anti-itch cream Genta had is alkaline, and can neutralise acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if I dip the cotton bud into it, and rub it on the upper part of the letter 'a' in the word 'Card' on the receipt...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.14,0:04:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! The 'a' turned into an 'o'!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.37,0:04:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.50,0:05:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.21,0:05:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, if I take the letters making up the words 'Card Purchases',
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.05,0:05:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and erase part of the 'a' and the whole 'd' from 'Card', as well as the 'urcha', and the final 's' from 'Purchases'...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Corpse'.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.09,0:05:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll tell them about the dead body!{loose}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.81,0:05:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, by strategically erasing part of the card number and phone number at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.13,0:05:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to show the number plate of the refrigerated van,\N I can convey that there's a dead body inside this van!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.47,0:05:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once I crumple this up a bit and stick it on Taii's collar like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.91,0:05:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then even if they manage to capture Taii and notice the receipt, they'd think it's just some sort of misprint,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.60,0:05:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or that the letters just rubbed off somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.61,0:05:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.76,0:05:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd come through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.89,0:06:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh. Looks like they stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.57,0:06:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Taii! Our lives depend on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.95,0:06:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must complete this mission at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.37,0:06:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.47,0:06:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a cat in the cargo area!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.25,0:06:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lemme guess, it probably snuck in when you left the doors wide open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.85,0:06:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the noise I heard earlier must've been this cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.50,0:06:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! There's paper in its collar!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.79,0:06:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.01,0:06:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.82,0:06:38.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.51,0:06:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It turned tail and fled!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.20,0:06:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we just have to rely on Taii!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.53,0:06:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.64,0:06:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.80,0:07:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's going to Poirot, then {\i1}that man{\i0} will see the code too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I made such a code — so {\i1}that man{\i0} would see it for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.50,0:07:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should figure it out straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.05,0:07:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he's one of the men in black...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.09,0:07:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bourbon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Taii! You're late today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.91,0:07:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drink it all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's that in your collar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.58,0:07:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A taxi receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Azusa-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master's{oy wasei} calling for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, aren't you a detective, Amuro-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then do you know what this means?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.57,0:08:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.70,0:08:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, never mind, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.85,0:08:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.16,0:08:18.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm freezing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.75,0:08:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the last one for the seventh district of Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make sure you get them to remember your name and face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we better go back to the second district to drop off that parcel that needs to be delivered at a specified time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and after that, I guess it's time to take the body back to his own house in the first district.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.61,0:08:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been ages since we let the cat go, \Nand nobody's coming to help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.84,0:08:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe that code was too difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.97,0:08:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe the piece of paper with the code slipped out of its collar midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.79,0:08:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that aside, what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.75,0:09:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't many parcels left to deliver, and we're running out of places to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.89,0:09:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. A pair like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.66,0:09:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you do something about them with your tranquilliser watch and kick booster shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.85,0:09:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing I thought as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.34,0:09:24.91,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,But on top of the fact that the watch is nearly out of battery, the cold's made the voltage go down and the thing's not even twitching!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.05,0:09:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been very quiet. Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I seem to have managed to get over the cold somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've stopped shivering, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait! That's even more dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.95,0:09:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.15,0:09:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.87,0:09:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's unconscious due to hypothermia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And his fingertips have gone purple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be long before he gets frostbite!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:09:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.65,0:10:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.50,0:10:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He lent Haibara his jacket, so he was only wearing one shirt after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.40,0:10:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.65,0:10:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.17,0:10:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.93,0:10:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.16,0:10:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.01,0:10:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were erased letters on the taxi receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.75,0:10:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that what you were trying to show me earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.32,0:10:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, as far as I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were empty spaces between 'Cor', 'P' and 'se', so I wondered if it was a misprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:36.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}C-O-R-P-S-E...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:39.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Corpse!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows that this cat comes here every day to beg for food?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He only started coming recently. So the only ones who know are me, the master, you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.21,0:10:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and apart from that, probably just Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.26,0:10:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan Edogawa-{\i1}kun{\i0}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, I touched its collar when I took the receipt, and it felt really cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I right in thinking it blew away in that direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.27,0:11:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You're going to look for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell the master I suddenly felt ill and had to go home early.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no need to pay me for today's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:35.71,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10}If I simulate the local area by taking into account the strength and direcion of the wind, and the positions of the buildings nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.17,0:11:40.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I should be able to model the wind currents and figure out where it was blown to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.00,0:11:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He woke up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.55,0:11:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:11:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.02,0:12:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You ended up suffering to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just stay still! I'll warm you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right! That's very kind of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.88,0:12:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with you guys like that, I doubt we'll be able to run away even if we tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we should be eating a great cake at the doc's by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.61,0:12:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the way from a cake shop in Yokohama!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.25,0:12:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yokohama?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.88,0:12:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cake being delivered to the Doc's is coming from a shop in Yokohama?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He specified for it to be delivered around the time we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.45,0:12:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This only happened because school finished early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.93,0:12:41.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.55,0:12:45.72,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10}those guys mentioned earlier that they were going back to the second district to deliver a parcel with a specified delivery time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you disturb things too much, they'll find out we're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the cake being delivered to the doc's house!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.64,0:12:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we gonna eat it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:12:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.60,0:13:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to stick a message on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using Mitsuhiko's pen and Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s cotton bud!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think you should write anything on the parcel, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.36,0:13:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imagine what would happen if those two found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.75,0:13:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we'd want it to be something the Doctor would notice immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine! He'll notice right away...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.35,0:13:28.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the delivery address isn't going to be the doc's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.96,0:13:37.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So the location was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:44.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's under the word 'Corpse' is probably a car's number plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:49.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The cat's collar was cold, so the most obvious conclusion would be a refrigerated car, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:56.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Specialised utility vehicles like that would have a plate number beginning with 8, and this number doesn't start with 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.06,0:14:01.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means it's most likely a cool goods delivery van.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:04.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And now that I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.22,0:14:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which house here belongs to 'Kudō'?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudō?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you gabbing about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The specified time parcel was for an 'Agasa', wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But just take a look! This sales slip...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.38,0:14:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says 'Care of Mr Kudō{samakata is translated as c/o, don't need another sama}' before Agasa, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange. It doesn't say that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.58,0:14:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! It looks like it's this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.28,0:14:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.47,0:14:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, but this is the Cheetah Delivery Service.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a Mr Hiroshi Agasa in residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Agasa-{\i1}san{\i0} lives next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.79,0:14:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we've got a parcel addressed to Hiroshi Agasa, care of Mr Kudō.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.28,0:14:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, now I remember. It's the cake, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:15:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's in the other room doing some work that he can't take his hands off of at the moment, so I'll take the parcel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wrote 'care of Mr Kudō' in front of 'Hiroshi Agasa'? And in ballpoint pen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.74,0:15:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.67,0:15:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the package won't go to the doc's, but should be delivered to Subaru-{\i1}san{\i0} living in the Kudō house next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.41,0:15:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.78,0:15:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you figured out a way for him to receive the parcel, but how did you tell him that we're in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody but me would write something like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.11,0:15:38.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he looks at the handwriting and the colour of the ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.28,0:15:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Subaru-{\i1}san{\i0} should easily be able to tell that it was added on later with a ballpoint pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.85,0:15:51.56,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,And he should also work out that the only way I could've written it would be from inside the delivery van out on its rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.56,0:15:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.87,0:16:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I spelt out our situation on the sales slip as well, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! But then we might be discovered at any moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:08.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wrote it using this cotton bud I removed the cotton from.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way you could write anything with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.41,0:16:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delivery sales slips usually have various layers,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.71,0:16:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,like the label, the sender's copy of it, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,[Receipt certificate]{blu: Proof of delivery}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,[Label]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,[Mail recipient]{blu: Recipient's copy}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're made using special paper so that if you write on the top one,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whatever you write is copied onto all the sheets underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if I remove the proof of delivery sheet that the postman would take out after having it signed by the recipient,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,write on the remaining two sheets with a cotton bud, then put the proof of delivery sheet back in,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.36,0:16:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,nobody will know I've written on the now bottom-most slip, the recipient's copy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.05,0:16:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until Subaru-{\i1}san{\i0} removes the label in front of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So right now those two guys are being dealt with by Subaru-{\i1}niichan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.03,0:16:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah. What Subaru-{\i1}san{\i0} would probably do is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.69,0:17:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why are you opening the back again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That recipient asked me to take on a small package.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.49,0:17:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only a small one, so you don't mind, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.50,0:17:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.30,0:17:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.60,0:17:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.08,0:17:28.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.89,0:17:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mobile phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably the most useful tool for us in this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.30,0:17:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.72,0:17:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The safest and most reliable way to catch these guys would be to explain our situation directly to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like we'd let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.41,0:17:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that some parcels had moved compared to earlier, so I decided I'd take a peek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:18:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what do you know, not just that cat, but five more sneaking kittens had snuck in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.37,0:18:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Didn't I tell you that I thought I heard a kid's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.81,0:18:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.40,0:18:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But these kids are pretty stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They should've phoned the police straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.97,0:18:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-So what should we do with these kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.82,0:18:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ain't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we take the phone off them, we just lock them in here and let them freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we line up their little bodies next to the geezer, and we'll have the ultimate impossible crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.65,0:18:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since these brats have no connection to us whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.56,0:18:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.60,0:18:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.77,0:18:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This road's rather narrow, so{lol Japanese double-entendres - I like DCTP's adaptations tho, so no issues :p -bluesun} could you please give way?{double: v.literal 'could you surrender something small?' double: something small being 'space for my car' / 'the children'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.38,0:18:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want to damage anything!{double: could also parse as 'I don't want to hurt you.'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.38,0:18:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the detective guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.05,0:18:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:19:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? What are you lot doing in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, this is just... err...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.79,0:19:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're a friend of the kids, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.13,0:19:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you've seen them, then there's no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanna stop them from getting killed, you better get in the van right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To give way because I didn't want to {\i1}damage{\i0} anything?{this is where the double comes back - 'Didn't I tell you? To give them up, as I don't want to hurt you.'}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to have a go as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.10,0:19:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yay!{/We did it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay. Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're an amazing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.73,0:19:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came here because you saw the code on the receipt, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:19:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Receipt?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that weird receipt in the cat's collar?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.52,0:20:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It got blown away by the wind and I couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be passing by this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.90,0:20:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aw, is that all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.05,0:20:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how about you come and eat cake with us in the Doctor's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.75,0:20:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the place of the famous Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.05,0:20:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I will have to decline for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.38,0:20:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have other things to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then give my regards to Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.10,0:22:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.69,0:22:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must've had quite a rough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.97,0:22:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was so cold I thought I'd freeze into an icicle!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.14,0:22:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko even passed out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.09,0:22:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.07,0:22:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0} warmed him up, so he felt better right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.44,0:22:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You caught the killers then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.33,0:22:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.58,0:22:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amuro-{\i1}san{\i0}, who works part-time at Poirot took care of them for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.58,0:22:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Amuro-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.80,0:22:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.51,0:22:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.91,0:22:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But never mind that, let's eat the cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.87,0:22:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went and forgot the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.35,0:22:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cake! Cake! Cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.10,0:23:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a special Christmas cake I ordered all the way from a famous bakery in Yokohama!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.28,0:23:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful not to make a mess eating!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.99,0:23:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feast your eyes on this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the icing on the cake?{literally, nande = what is this?! + decoration = nandecoration - horrible pun}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.42,0:23:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.31,0:23:31.07,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10}Now that I think about it, they did say something about dropping parcels on purpose so that recipients remembered them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.54,0:23:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red diamond on this turtle's back — the Blush Mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.82,0:23:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true! It's stuck to the turtle's back, gold necklace chain and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.70,0:23:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, it's quite the guard you have here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.28,0:23:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.86,0:23:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Kaitō Kid'!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.20,0:23:57.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How'd he manage to do it in a situation like {\i1}this{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.96,0:24:04.96,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART I)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.96,0:24:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'Kaitō Kid and the Blush Mermaid (Part I)'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: The huge water tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.96,0:24:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Amuro-{\i1}san{\i0}'s a really nice person!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.22,0:24:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Edogawa-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.24,0:24:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Don't ask me.
